#: ../../api/jinwu.lightcurve.LightcurveSNREvaluator.rst:2
msgid "LightcurveSNREvaluator"
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:1 of
msgid "Evaluate whether a given lightcurve can reach a target SNR after T0."
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:3 of
msgid ""
"This class takes a binned ON-region lightcurve (time edges or centers and"
" counts per bin) and a background prior, finds T0 via Bayesian Blocks "
"using per-block Li&Ma SNR≥3, then computes the maximum Li&Ma SNR within a"
" fixed time window after T0. It supports a fast expected-value mode and "
"an MC mode with Poisson fluctuations for ON and OFF."
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:10 of
msgid "Typical usage"
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:27 of
msgid "Load from NPZ (common keys)"
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:28 of
msgid "The loader prefers the following keys if present: - counts (ON-region):"
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:30 of
msgid "'corrected_counts_src'  (preferred; counts in source region per bin)"
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:31 of
msgid ""
"If only net+background available: 'corrected_counts' (net) and "
"'corrected_counts_back' (OFF region) then ON counts reconstructed by: "
"counts_on = net + area_ratio * back"
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.duration.LightcurveSNREvaluator:34 of
msgid ""
"As a fallback, 'raw_corrected_counts' will be treated as ON counts "
"(approximation if it's actually net); a warning is emitted."
msgstr ""

